author: Branch Education
description:
You've probably used a keyboard for at least a few hours today, but have you ever wondered what's inside it and how it works? Well, in this video, we're going to tear apart a typical keyboard and see all the parts inside. Specifically, this keyboard is NOT a mechanical keyboard; it's a membrane keyboard. In total, this keyboard costs just $6.00, and it's so cheap because it's only made of a few parts.

If you're curious as to how keyboards work, watch the full video - https://youtu.be/h-NM1xSSzHQ
title: How does an Everyday Keyboard Work? ⌨️🤔 #keyboard  #pcbuild
